 \frac{1}{e^{j\theta} - A} - p =  \frac{1-\overline{A} e^{j\theta}}{(e^{j\theta}-A)(1-|A|^2)}
\left|1 - \overline{A} e^{j\theta}\right| = \left|e^{j\theta} (e^{-j\theta} - \overline{A})\right| = \left|e^{j\theta}-A\right|
\left| \frac{1}{e^{j\theta} - A} - p \right| = \frac{1}{|1-|A|^2|}
